    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>[4 Bryanston Street, London.]</placeName>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
                    <p>I can entertain no doubt that you are excellently fitted to fill the chair of Geology in the U. of Edinburgh.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> I have read with care &amp; great interest your two last works relating on the later geological periods which are probably the most difficult of all to investigate;<ref target="#foot.f3"/> &amp; after reading these works, I am convinced that you will be able to excite in the minds of all students a keen interest in the science of Geology, &amp; this is the corner-stone in the work of teaching.—</p>
                    <p>Earnestly wishing you success, I remain | my dear Sir | yours very faithfully | Ch. D</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
